body: @jywu-msft is this going to be addressed with your upcoming update for better handling of unexpected EP failures?

> @jywu-msft is this going to be addressed with your upcoming update for better handling of unexpected EP failures?

no, this is unrelated to the python fallback to cpu.  1) because it's not python 2) the upcoming fallback will run the entire graph on CPU.

OP is saying he would like to fall back to CUDA or CPU for an unsupported subgraph. 
this error is typically due to onnx-tensorrt parser bug which reports subgraph can be executed by TensorRT (when it can't) which prevents ORT from assigning the subgraph to a different provider.
@stevenlix , can you take a look at the sample model?

Additional information: the session can be created and executed if I swap the order (append CUDA, then append TensoRT). I guess CUDA EP took care of the parts that causing the issue?

@stevenlix Is this possibly due to not checking the return value from nvonnxparser::IParser::supportsModel?

Re: swapping the registration order,
effectively, you're assigning CUDA EP a higher priority than TensorRT EP. It will be assigned the problematic nodes in the graph (that TensorRT EP was having problems with)

@GuanLuo  Hi, can you share your CMakeLists.txt how to found these header files? I can not found these path in onnxruntime include folder structures.

Here is what I did to construct the include folder, `/workspace/onnxruntime` is the git repository
```
mkdir -p /usr/local/include/onnxruntime && \
        cp /workspace/onnxruntime/include/onnxruntime/core/session/onnxruntime_c_api.h \
            /usr/local/include/onnxruntime && \
        cp /workspace/onnxruntime/include/onnxruntime/core/providers/cpu/cpu_provider_factory.h \
            /usr/local/include/onnxruntime && \
        cp /workspace/onnxruntime/include/onnxruntime/core/providers/cuda/cuda_provider_factory.h \
            /usr/local/include/onnxruntime && \
        cp /workspace/onnxruntime/include/onnxruntime/core/providers/tensorrt/tensorrt_provider_factory.h \
            /usr/local/include/onnxruntime && \
```
@GuanLuo please pull latest onnxruntime. I tried the sample model and all nodes in it are supported by TRT
@stevenlix sorry for not getting back to you, thank you for making the nodes supported by TensorRT. And I assume that the fallback mechanism is also working for TensorRT EP now?
@GuanLuo were you able to get this working? let us know if you still need any further assistance or if the issue can be closed. thanks!
@faxu Yes this issue can be closed.
